 (0.00 ":irc.foonet.org 324 tester #chan +Cnt")
 (0.01 ":irc.foonet.org 329 tester #chan 1738379988")
 (0.07 ":alice!~u@pgq8itg3w7n3a.irc PRIVMSG #chan :bob: Grows, lives, and dies, in single blessedness.")
 (0.05 ":bob!~u@pgq8itg3w7n3a.irc PRIVMSG #chan :alice: Is't come to this, i' faith ? Hath not the world one man but he will wear his cap with suspicion ? Shall I never see a bachelor of three-score again ? Go to, i' faith; an thou wilt needs thrust thy neck into a yoke, wear the print of it, and sigh away Sundays. Look! Don Pedro is returned to seek you.")
 (0.05 ":alice!~u@pgq8itg3w7n3a.irc PRIVMSG #chan :There's the fool hangs on your back already.")
 (0.07 ":alice!~u@pgq8itg3w7n3a.irc PRIVMSG #chan :bob: Here is a purr of Fortune's, sir, or of Fortune's cat but not a musk-cat that has fallen into the unclean fishpond of her displeasure, and, as he says, is muddied withal. Pray you, sir, use the carp as you may, for he looks like a poor, decayed, ingenious, foolish, rascally knave. I do pity his distress in my similes of comfort, and leave him to your lordship."))
